Non-exhaustive unsorted list of stuff left to do:

* distinguish between build tools, host tools and target tools (libs)
* take the stamp mechanism from stage2
* support distinct host definition
* rename this as the latest when compatibility to stage2 breaks
* support selection from multiple gcc / glibc versions
* add DejaGnu package for compiler tests
* support the GCC testsuite from https://github.com/gcc-mirror/gcc/tree/master/gcc/testsuite
* make target definition more flexible (kconfig?)
* build qemu to support target tests for native cross builds
* support install pattern to be able reduce package size
* support download cache population
* support download url overrides
* check dependencies, possible reference: http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/view/development/appendices/dependencies.html

